   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-PALESTINIANS (Rafah, Gaza Strip) _ Cruising at 19,000
feet on Saturday in the cockpit of the first Palestinian Airlines
flight to depart from the new international airport in the Gaza
Strip, Capt. Jamal Al-How from the Jabaliya refugee camp could not
restrain himself. ``At this historic moment, taking off for the
first time in history from a Palestinian airport, all the languages
of the world cannot express my pride and joy,'' he declared. By
Joel Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   NATO-MEETING (Washington) _ Advance on the upcoming meeting to
discuss the future of NATO. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   VENEZUELA-VOTE (Caracas, Venezuela) _ Venezuelans vote for a
president, and the front-runner is Hugo Chavez, a 44-year-old
retired army officer who once led a bloody coup attempt. By Diana
Jean Schemo. (Story will likely appear on Page 1 if the results are
definitive.)
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TEAMSTERS-RDP (Washington) _ Most of the time, there is
rejoicing in the labor movement when a forceful, articulate leader
is elected to head a powerful union. But this weekend there was
plenty of ambivalence because the leader's last name is Hoffa. By
Steven Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-RDP (WASHINGTON) _ Developments on the impeachment
front. The House Judiciary Committee offered to give the White
House two days this week to present the president's side in the
Monica Lewinsky case. By Lizette Alvarez.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LAYOFFS-NEWSTYLE (Indianapolis) _ Plant closings and layoffs are
rising sharply again. The cutbacks announced recently at Bankers
Trust and Boeing are only the latest examples. But the outcries and
conflict that characterized the waves of downsizing in the 1980s
and early 1990s are gone. Rather than protest, unions are more
likely now to help their laid-off members make the transition to
other jobs. By Louis Uchitelle. (With a graphic.)
</P>
