contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   GETTY-DISPUTE (Los Angeles) _ In tony Pacific Palisades, the
privileges of affluence are clashing with the ambitions of high
culture over proposed expansion of the history J. Paul Getty
museum. ``We probably have enough culture already,'' said resident
Cie Allman. ``The Palisades is not a Mecca. We want to be left
alone. That's why people like Tom Cruise, Tom Hanks and Arnold
Schwarzenegger live here. By Phillip W. Browne. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
