``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   VALLEY-APARTMENTS (Los Angeles) _ City officials are planning to
accommodate a massive population boom primarily by providing
high-density apartments to low-income families, with much of this
proposed in traditionally middle-income, single-family
neighborhoods in the San Fernando Valley. By Beth Barrett. (Will
move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
