r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GEN-HOFFARTH-COLUMN-L     12-06 0632
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-HOFFARTH-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOME UPS, MOSTLY DOWNS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In case you were Pond slummin' it, college
football's weekend in review:
</P>
<P>
   Saturday: Astounding.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday: All atwitter.
</P>
<P>
   Today through Jan. 4: Anticlimactic, with scattered acid raining
down on Columbus, Tucson and Manhattan, Kan.
</P>
<P>
   Knock off Texas A&AMP;M, and K-State woulda still been
underqualified even to send its trombone section to the Fiesta
parade. Even that goal-line ref was doing the raise-the-roof call
on the A&AMP;M overtime TD.
</P>
<P>
   The Aggies did everyone a huge favor by gagging Bill Snyder once
and for all. And this has nothing to do with media bias about his
62nd-rated schedule that somehow avoided Take A Nap Tech.
</P>
<P>
   Now run along and play Tulane in the No Respect Bowl, and phone
in the result to your weekly throwaway. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ Final BCS rankings are available at your local ATM machine.
Put in the card, punch in the code U-C-L-A, watch what happens.
</P>
<P>
   Hint: You get nothin'. Unless you're Bob Toledo , in which case
you get quick cash and buy a new defensive game plan. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ True then, true now: Cade McNown on the BCS before the Miami
game: ``To be honest, until everything is decided on the field in a
playoff, it's all pretty much of a joke.'' . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ If it's any consolation, Phoenix in January is . . . well . .
. pretty darn pleasant, actually. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ Getting home-field advantage back can't be all stinky, unless
Bruins backers start giving up their luxurious Rose Bowl seats
again for the privilege of staying home and watching it hung-over.
And don't think !ital!that won't happen. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ Hey, stinking Badgers _ got a few Pasadena travel packages
lined up right here, !ital!guar-un-teed to fall through at the last
minute. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ That craps game going on in Vegas with John ``Rebel With a
Lost Cause'' Robinson turned on him at the press conference when
UNLV introduced him as its new head coach.
</P>
<P>
   Someone asked how much money he'd be making. Robinson said it
was a ``private matter.'' UNLV president Carol Harter reminded him
that since this ain't no private high-falootin' university, his
contract has to be made public _ three years, $135,000 per.
</P>
<P>
   JR, we're just as embarrassed that info got out as you are. . .
.
</P>
<P>
   _ Meanwhile, Lou Holtz has induced about $600,000 a pop from the
 &UR; !ital! &LR; other USC to leave his cushy TV job that wasn't paying him
that much less. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ It's the end of the WAC as we know it, and I feel fine. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ Kevin Brown circles through Southern California this week to
entertain the possibility of being signed by the Angels or Dodgers,
but don't make too much of it. This has been homecoming month for
major-league pitchers. Randy Johnson touches down in Phoenix, Roger
Clemens wants to go to Houston, Orel Hershiser is trying to tell
Tampa Bay and Florida that he'd like to retire there. Brown says he
wants to play near his nest in Georgia, though best bet is him
staying kaput in San Diego. . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ This Showtime Dec. 19 NBA exhibition that'll be announced
today, co-pushed by player agents David Falk and Arn Tellem, will
be as anticipated as the pay-per-few one-on-one between Shaq Daddy
and Hakeem the Dream that actually never made it off the ground. .
. .
</P>
<P>
   _ Always good for a quote Billy Packer , on why there's no
complaint from fans about the NBA-less winter: ``They developed
entertainment fans, not basketball fans. That's why you're not
hearing much outcry because those fans have turned to movies or
music for the entertainment.'' . . .
</P>
<P>
   _ And another weekend has passed where there were no blown calls
by NFL referees during games involving L.A. teams. . . . &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
