<HEADLINE>
GEORGE CROTHERS, 89, TELEVISION PRODUCER 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dr. George D. Crothers, the producer of the long-running CBS
television religious program ``Lamp Unto My Feet,'' died on Nov. 27
in Sarasota, Fla., where he lived. He was 89.
</P>
<P>
   Crothers was born in Fort Morgan, Colo., and lived in Sarasota
for 22 years. He graduated from Wooster College in Wooster, Ohio,
and received his doctorate in modern European history from Columbia
University.
</P>
<P>
   He taught at Columbia until 1946, when he joined CBS in New
York, working for 30 years on public affairs programming. He was
director of religious broadcasts at CBS and a producer of ``Lamp
Unto My Feet,'' which ran on Sunday mornings from 1948 to 1979.
</P>
<P>
   He is survived by his wife, Angelica; a son, Michael, of
Congers, N.Y.; four grandchildren, and five great-grandchildren.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
