<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC TO FACE TCU
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   USC's anticipated rematch with Purdue suddenly didn't look so
bad Sunday, when the Sun Bowl voted to select Texas Christian as
the Trojans' opponent for the Dec.31 bowl game in El Paso.
</P>
<P>
   Texas Christian became USC's opponent after Ohio State was
selected by the BCS on Sunday, meaning Purdue moved up a notch and
will play in the Alamo Bowl. Earlier this week, Purdue had accepted
an invitation to the Sun Bowl, but UCLA and Kansas State's losses
Saturday shook up the BCS bowl pairings.
</P>
<P>
   The Horned Frogs (6-5, 4-4) are a less-than-exhilarating choice,
considering they are unranked and barely qualified for a bowl game
by defeating 0-11 Nevada-Las Vegas in their season finale.
</P>
<P>
   Sun Bowl executive director John Folmer said Sunday that Texas
Christian was selected over Central Florida. Colorado State,
Wyoming and Miami of Ohio were also last-minute considerations.
</P>
<P>
   Folmer had negotiated Saturday with the Southeastern Conference
to take Alabama, Georgia or Arkansas, but said that plan fell
through when Florida was taken by the BCS to play in the Orange
Bowl. That meant the SEC had no extra teams to send to bowls after
filling its contractual agreements.
</P>
<P>
   ``Several of those SEC teams wanted to play USC,'' Folmer said.
``We were held hostage by the BCS and the Big Ten. Unfortunately,
this system has flaws. It was not very much fun Saturday. We had a
wacky last 24 hours.''
</P>
<P>
   TCU was favored by the Sun Bowl because it is expected to bring
a sizable contingent to the game, and because coach Dennis
Franchione is well-known in El Paso after coaching at nearby New
Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's two up-and-coming teams,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said.
``It wasn't a matter of who we were going to play. We're just
delighted to keep playing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our programs are similar. We were both down a little bit. I
just don't want it to be too much of a home game with them.''
</P>
<P>
   The Horned Frogs are led by All-WAC linebacker Joseph Phipps,
who has 152 tackles and 5.5 sacks. Their top offensive player is
tailback Basil Mitchell, who gained more than 1,000 yards this
season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
